RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 1 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 71. Maiden Special Weight Purse 31000. FOR MN-BRED MAIDENS, THREE, FOUR, AND FIVE YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: R VOO'S TABOO pressed the early pace from a two wide stance, gained command near the quarter pole, and shook clear in homestretch for a convincing score. EYE ON RY settled in behind the pacesetting duo and gave chase from a two wide pose, angled out to the three path at upper stretch and finished willingly to earn the place. WYNN TRIP broke alertly, set the pace while saving ground, then failed to fend off the top pair in the final furlong. SWEET BODEMEISTER lacked a serious bid after coming away tardily, giving chase from an inside stance, and swinging wide at upper stretch.

ENTRY.NAME: Sweet Bodemeister
ENTRY.COMMENT: tardy break,chased inside, wide upper, no late bid

ENTRY.NAME: Eye On Ry
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased two wide, three path upper, up for place

ENTRY.NAME: R Voo's Taboo
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed two wide, led quarter pole, shook clear

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 2 5F Turf CR: 74. Claiming Purse 12000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR MINNESOTA BRED WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000. Minnesota Bred Claiming Price $15,000. (If management d eems it inadvisable to run this race on the Turf, it will be run at a distance of 5 Furlongs on the main track.) (Rail at 30 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SIXTH STREET (FR) chased the leaders down the backstretch before being roused entering the turn, then made a mid move and weaved through traffic to be on even terms and three wide at upper stretch before finishing mid track with strongest stride late for the victory. THORN CROWN pressed the early pace while trekking the three path, was two wide and on in concert at uper stretch, engaged in a stretch duel with rallying rival, but was outdueled in the end. MISS MAC MAC rushed form outset and set the pace from a ground saving stance, was on even terms as the inner rival at upper stretch, then gave way to dueling duo in final furlong. BAILOUT KELA broke alertly and pressed the pace as the outer most rival of four abreast along the backstretch, lost gorund to front runners with a wide journey, then lacked a needed rally in the late strides. PURRFECT MOON settled into mid pack and saved ground around the bend before angling out to two wide at upper stretch but failed to threaten the leaders. CHAPARRITA showed reserve from outset, traveled widest of all around the turn, and passed a tiring in closing strides. LET ME DOWN EASY pressed the early pace along the backstretch before fading fast inside the quarter pole.

ENTRY.NAME: Sixth Street (FR)
ENTRY.COMMENT: mid move, weaved traffic, three wide upper, strong kick mid track

ENTRY.NAME: Purrfect Moon
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased inside, swung two wide upper, no threat

ENTRY.NAME: Miss Mac Mac
ENTRY.COMMENT: pace inside, gave way to dueling duo

ENTRY.NAME: Thorn Crown
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed three path, brief lead, outdueled

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 3 6F Dirt CR: 83. Allowance Purse 28000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR MINNESOTA BRED WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CROCODILE TEARS hustled away from outset and set the pace from between rivals, gained sole command through the turn, was saving ground at upper stretch, then inched away from all challengers in the final furlong. LO LO'S LAUGHTER showed interest in early command and set the pace in concert as the outer of three abreast, rated on the heels of the leader at upper stretch, but was no match for the rival in the closing strides. MY CRAZY NEIGHBOR settled into mid pack down the backstretch, trekked three wide through the bend and into the homestretch, then rallied mildly for the show. HAPPY DANCER settled into mid pack through the opening half while trekking the three path before being nipped in closing strides for the show. IRISH DAWN pressed the pace from outset while travelling four wide, maintained that line through the bend and steadily lost ground to leaders while doing so. JRUE BREEZE was unhurried in the early going, rated between foes and in the second flight at upper stretch, and lacked a needed rally in homestretch. CASEY'S LAW flashed early speed and rated close up through the opening call as the inner most rival before steadily fading inside the half pole.

ENTRY.NAME: Happy Dancer
ENTRY.OWNER: Lund Valorie Aithon Stable LLC Naistat Richard Naistat Beverly Rapoport Ron Heus
ENTRY.COMMENT: mid pack, three path journey, nipped for show

ENTRY.NAME: Lo Lo's Laughter
ENTRY.COMMENT: three wide early, two path upper, no match

ENTRY.NAME: My Crazy Neighbor
ENTRY.COMMENT: mid pack, three wide quarter pole, mild rally

ENTRY.NAME: Irish Dawn
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed four wide, lost ground with wide trip

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 4 1 3/8M Turf CR: 95. Starter Optional Claiming Purse 15000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $5,000 (MINNESOTA BRED $7,500) OR LESS IN 2022 - 2023 OR CLAIMING PRICE $10,000. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At One Mile Or Over Since July 16 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000 (Claiming Races For $8,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances). Minnesota Bred Claiming Price $15,000. (If management deems it inadvisable to run this race on the Turf, it will be run at a distance of 1 Mile and 1/4 on the main track.) (Rail at 30 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CASHANOVA tucked to save ground shortly after the start, stalked the front runners through the opening turn, was within striking distance at the midway point, then rallied along the rail in final quarter for the score. WAR CHEST settled into mid pack and took a two path trip to the half pole before swinging three wide at upper stretch while under rousing, then engaged in a stretch duel in final furlong but was edged by that rival for the honors. NOBLE PURSUIT chose to show reserve in the early stages before angling out four wide at upper stretch and engaging in a stretch duel near the eighth pole, but was outfinished in closing strides. SUPER WISE stalked the early pacesetter by leading the second flight through the opening half, trekked the three path through the final bend, rated close up at upper stretch, but failed to match strides with rivals in the final furlong. THIRTY SECONDS OUT rushed from outset to lead the field while saving ground, maintained command into the homestretch, then folded in final furlong. ZUMURUDEE showed patience by trailing the field through the opening half before being roused nearing the half pole, swinging widest of all at upper stretch and lacking a needed rally in homestretch. CLUB MESQUITE settled into mid pack and trekked the three path through the opening mile before tiring in the latter portion of contest.

ENTRY.NAME: Zumurudee
ENTRY.OWNER: Woolley Jr Bennie L and Eklund Jack

ENTRY.NAME: Club Mesquite
ENTRY.COMMENT: mid pack, three path trip, tired

ENTRY.NAME: Super Wise
ENTRY.COMMENT: second flight, close up quarter pole, failed to sustain

ENTRY.NAME: War Chest
ENTRY.COMMENT: two path trip, three wide upper, outdueled

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 5 6F Dirt CR: 92. Claiming Purse 19500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES SINCE FEBRUARY 16 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000. Minnesota Bred Claiming Price $30,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: INTER MIAMI broke alertly and established a ground saving stance jut off the early pace, circled the pacesetter two wide near the quarter pole, gained command at upper stretch, and finished under a stiff drive for the score. BLAME J D loomed mid pack through the first call, took a wide journey around the bend, then closed with a rush to earn the place while gaining on leader at finish. WINDCRACKER rallied mildly for the show to end a ground saving journey. SEA TO SUCCESS rated mid pack through the opening half while trekking the three path and finished evenly. MACHO ROCCO pressed the early pace from a three wide pose, rated close up at upper stretch, then weakened in final sixteenth. STORMIN HONGKONG trailed from outset before passing a tiring rival in late strides. PRIZE FIGHTER flashed early foot and led the field to upper stretch while saving ground before eclipsing in the homestretch.

ENTRY.NAME: Inter Miami
ENTRY.COMMENT: circled leader two wide quarter pole, driving

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 6 7 1/2F Turf CR: 64. Maiden Claiming Purse 10500. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE, FOUR, AND FIVE YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000. Minnesota Bred Claiming Price $15,000. (If management deems it inadvisable to run this race on the turf, two-year-old races will be run at 6 and 1/2 furlongs and races for three-year-olds and up will be run at a distance of 1 mile on the main track.) (Rail at 30 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DIXIE GIRL TO broke alertly, gained command before entering the opening bend, tucked to save ground, and shook clear in the end. MARK OF VICTORY settled into second flight along the inside, saved ground all the way, and finished a clear second but could not catch tough winner in the end. DR Z'S ELSA showed reserve through the opening half, advanced with a mid move by trekking widest of all through the closing bend, rated close up at upper stretch, and held onto the show in the end but failed to match stride with top pair in final furlong. GRACEFUL MOON was of little threat while travelling three wide and rating back. IT'S ME rushed form outset to press the pace from a three wide pose, led the second flight along the backstretch, then failed to sustain the bid in crucial strides. TAMMY MACHO showed interest in early command by rushing from outset, rated close up between rivals through the opening turn before checking at head of backstretch and steadily weakening thereafter.

ENTRY.NAME: Dixie Girl To
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke alertly, saved ground, shook clear

ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed three wide, failed to match

ENTRY.NAME: Dr Z's Elsa
ENTRY.COMMENT: reserved, mid move, close up upper, held show

ENTRY.NAME: Tammy Macho
ENTRY.COMMENT: early interest, checked at head of backstretch

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Northlands Juvenile Final CANTERBURY PARK RACE 7 350 Y Dirt CR: 67. Final Purse 15000. FOR QUARTER HORSES, TWO YEARS OLD WHICH WERE ENTERED IN THE 2023 NORTHLANDS FUTURITY TRIALS AND DID NOT QUALLIFY FOR THE FINAL. $15,000 Guaranteed. Weight: 124 lbs. Preference by time from the Northlands Futurity trials. Horses that are entered into the t rials but fail to earn a time will be least preferred. The final purse will be reduced by the cost of any Out of Competition testing required by the Minnesota Racing Commission as a condition of competing in this race. Trials were run Wednesday, August 2. .
